718440f-c.text:

Street, showing half-completed Century Apartments being erected

718441f.title: Manhattan: Central Park West - 62nd Street (West)
718441f.text:
Central Park West, west side, from West 62nd
to 63rd Street's, showing the New Theatre, which
later became the Century Opera House. This building,
designed by Carrere and Hastings, was completed in
1908-9. This photo, or a similar one appeared in the
December, 1909 issue of"Architecture." An account of
the proposed plans will be found in the New York Sun-
Sunday--July 24, 1906.
1909
0ift of Urbrock Collection
Copyright-1909
By George P. Hnull & Son

718442f-a.title: Manhattan: Central Park West - 62nd Street (West)
718442f-a.text:
Central Park West, west side, between West 62nd and 63rd Streets. Prom-
inent building shown with the Twin Towers, is the Century Apartments, (No. 25
Central Park West). On the right appears a portion of the Hotel Mayflower
(S.W. corner of West 62nd Street), and on the left, the Society for Ethical
Culture (N.W. corner of West 63rd Street), with the West 63rd Street Branch of
the Y.M.C.A. at its rear. This view is taken from Central Park; the east s ide
of this street.
1936.
W.P.A. Photo.
Federal Writers Project.

718235f-a.title: Manhattan: Central Park West - 62nd Street
718235f-a.text:
Central Park: The Lake and westerly building outline.
The latter is formed by the apartment structures that line
the thoroughfare, Central Park West. Dominant on 4ame is
the twin towered San Remo Apartments. This occupies the
74th-75th Street frontage. At the left is the outstanding
Century Apartments at 62nd-63rd Street
July 1930
July 1931
George L. Balgue
